# Add actuator source plots (motors, servos, outputs) with flat-top FFT

## Context
The script already has "source" plots (`motor_rpm_sources.png`, `motor_current_sources.png`,
`motor_pwm_sources.png`) built by `_plot_source_panel` / `plot_vibration_sources` —
time series on top, PSD on bottom, all related channels overlaid. We want the same
two-panel view for the autopilot's per-channel actuator commands:
`actuator_motors.control[*]`, `actuator_servos.control[*]`, and
`actuator_outputs[*].output[*]`. These show what the mixer / control allocator is
commanding each motor/servo/output and how that demand is distributed in frequency.

Key difference from the existing source plots: the user wants the **same FFT as the
imu_fft plots** — the flat-top single-FFT `direct_fft` (l.~132), **not** the Welch PSD
that `_plot_source_panel` currently uses.

Verified in the log (`log_1_2026-4-29-13-48-36.ulg`):
- `actuator_motors` (plural), single instance, `control[0..11]`; only `control[0]`/
  `control[1]` populated, `control[2..11]` all-NaN. ~5 Hz (dt ≈ 197 ms).
- `actuator_servos` (plural), single instance, `control[0..7]`; `control[0..5]` active,
  `control[6]`/`control[7]` constant. ~5 Hz.
- `actuator_outputs`, **two instances (multi_id 1 and 2)**, `output[0..15]`, **no
  `timestamp_sample`**, ~100 Hz (dt ≈ 9.94 ms, Nyquist ≈ 50 Hz).
  - Instance 1: only output[0]/output[1] vary, saturating to 65535 (the "raw"/idle instance).
  - Instance 2: output[0..6] vary with realistic PWM (≈360–700 µs).

Decisions (confirmed with user):
- Skip non-varying channels: drop all-NaN and near-zero-variance channels.
- Time base: prefer `timestamp_sample` (fall back to `timestamp`), shifted by `T_OFFSET`.
  (motors/servos have it; actuator_outputs falls back to `timestamp`.)
- `actuator_outputs_*` → emit **one plot per instance**, named with the multi_id.
- Output filenames: `actuator_motor_sources.png`, `actuator_servo_sources.png`,
  `actuator_outputs_<i>_sources.png`.
- Channel overlay + 2-panel layout identical to `motor_current_sources.png`.
- The existing `motor_pwm_sources.png` (Welch, single picked instance) stays as-is;
  these new direct-FFT per-instance output plots are additive.

## Changes — `analyze_imu_vibration.py`

### 1. Extend `_plot_source_panel` with an `fft_kind` arg (backward-compatible)
Current signature: `_plot_source_panel(t, channels, title, units, outpath, t0, t1)`.
- New signature: add `fft_kind="welch"` (default preserves existing motor/ESC/PWM plots).
- **NaN-safe channel skip:** in the per-channel loop, after `seg = sig[mask]`, add
  `if not np.isfinite(seg).all(): continue` *before* the existing `np.std(seg) < 1e-6`
  check. (NaN channels currently slip past the variance check since `nan < 1e-6` is
  False; this only removes channels that would otherwise plot as NaN — safe for
  existing callers.)
- **PSD branch:** replace the single `welch(...)` call with:
  ```python
  if fft_kind == "direct":
      freqs, _, psd = direct_fft(seg, fs)        # flat-top, same as imu_fft plots
  else:
      freqs, psd = welch(seg, fs=fs, window="hann", nperseg=nperseg,
                         noverlap=nperseg // 2, scaling="density", detrend="constant")
  ```
- **Suptitle:** make the method + resolution adapt:
  ```python
  if fft_kind == "direct":
      method, res = "flat-top FFT", (fs / n_in)
  else:
      method, res = "Welch", (fs / nperseg)
  fig.suptitle(f"{title}  —  {method}, window t={t0:.1f}–{t1:.1f}s, "
               f"fs≈{fs:.0f} Hz, Δf≈{res:.2f} Hz")
  ```
  (`nperseg` stays computed for the Welch path; unused in the direct path.)
- Everything else (time-series top panel, xlim `0..fs/2`, axis labels, legends) unchanged.

### 2. New function: `plot_actuator_control_sources(ulog, outdir, t0, t1)`
Add next to `plot_vibration_sources`. Drives all three topics from one spec list;
generalizes the channel-key prefix (`control[` vs `output[`) and handles per-instance.
```python
def plot_actuator_control_sources(ulog, outdir, t0, t1):
    """Per-channel actuator command sources, overlaid, with the same flat-top
    direct_fft used by the imu_fft plots (time series top, PSD bottom). Mirrors
    the motor_current_sources layout.
      actuator_motors.control[*]      -> actuator_motor_sources.png
      actuator_servos.control[*]      -> actuator_servo_sources.png
      actuator_outputs[i].output[*]   -> actuator_outputs_<i>_sources.png (per instance)
    """
    specs = [
        ("actuator_motors", "control[", "norm", "actuator_motor_sources.png",
         "actuator_motors control per channel", False),
        ("actuator_servos", "control[", "norm", "actuator_servo_sources.png",
         "actuator_servos control per channel", False),
        ("actuator_outputs", "output[", "PWM", None, None, True),
    ]
    for topic, prefix, units, fname, title, per_instance in specs:
        instances = all_instances(ulog, topic)
        if not instances:
            print(f"[act_sources] no {topic}; skipping")
            continue
        for d in instances:
            if "timestamp_sample" in d.data:
                t = d.data["timestamp_sample"].astype(np.int64) / 1e6 - T_OFFSET
            else:
                t = t_seconds(d, ulog)
            keys = sorted((k for k in d.data if k.startswith(prefix)),
                          key=lambda s: int(s[len(prefix):-1]))
            if not keys:
                continue
            channels = {k: d.data[k] for k in keys}
            if per_instance:
                out_fname = f"{topic}_{d.multi_id}_sources.png"
                out_title = f"{topic}[{d.multi_id}] output per channel"
            else:
                out_fname, out_title = fname, title
            _plot_source_panel(t, channels, out_title, units,
                               outdir / out_fname, t0, t1, fft_kind="direct")
```

### 3. Wire into `main()`
After the `plot_vibration_sources(ulog, OUTDIR, t0, t1)` call add:
```python
plot_actuator_control_sources(ulog, OUTDIR, t0, t1)
```

### 4. Update module docstring
Add to the Outputs list (near the other `*_sources.png` entries):
- `actuator_motor_sources.png        : actuator_motors control[*] time-series + flat-top FFT PSD`
- `actuator_servo_sources.png        : actuator_servos control[*] time-series + flat-top FFT PSD`
- `actuator_outputs_<i>_sources.png  : actuator_outputs[i] output[*] time-series + flat-top FFT PSD`

## Reused, not reinvented
- `_plot_source_panel` (extended) — same 2-panel layout as `motor_current_sources.png`.
- `direct_fft` (l.~132) — the exact flat-top FFT the imu_fft plots use.
- `all_instances` (l.88), `get_topic` (l.82), `t_seconds` (l.91), `T_OFFSET` shift,
  and the `timestamp_sample` time-base idiom from `plot_timing_vehicle_imu` (l.~524).

